Day 2
======

variables & data types
---------------------

variable is a container that can hold data

before creating variable we need to mention the data type

Two type of data types -> Primitive and Non Primitive

Primitive
---------
byte, short, int, long ---> numbers without decimal
float, double ---> decimal numbers
char ---> single character 'x'
boolean ---> true/ false

Non primitive/ Derived/ Collections
----------------------------------
String
ArrayList
HashMap
HashSet etc

Primitive types-->
byte        1 byte      -128 to 127
short       2 bytes     -32,768 to 32,767
int         4 bytes     -2,147,483,648 to 2,147,483,647
long        8 bytes     -9,223,372,036,854,775,808 to 9,223,372,036,854,775,807

float       4 bytes     fractional numbers upto 7 decimal
double      8 bytes     fractional numbers upto 15 decimal

boolean     1 bit       true or false
char        2 bytes     Single char / letter


Java is statically typed prog language
python is dynamic

eg:

int x = 100;
x="welcome"    // this is not possible in java but can in python
in java we can change the value, but not the data type

in python we don't specify the data type explicitly

-END-